# API rules for relations · pocketbase/pocketbase · Discussion #5604
created: 2024-10-05, last updated: 2026-04-16, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/5604)

OR alternatively using `@request.auth.*` back-relation:
```
@request.auth.id != "" &&
// prevent assigning themself as admin member because the Create API rule runs AFTER dry submit of the record
@request.data.member != @request.auth.id &&
@request.auth.group_members_via_member.group ?= @request.data.group &&
@request.auth.group_members_via_member.role ?= "admin"
```
The second rule requires the extra `@request.data.member != @request.auth.id` check because currently the Create API rule runs AFTER a dry submit of the record, aka.
when performing the self-join the record will aready exist in the `group_members` table.
...
So the overall rule would read like that:
- `group.group_members_via_group.member ?= @request.auth.id` = there must be at least one group’s member with the user id
- `group.group_members_via_group.status ?!= "invited"` = and none of those ⬆️ group members have the invited status

